   Welcome to the US District Court, Northern District of Ohio

   Public Notices

   [clearpixel.gif]

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   The Local Rules were modified on 12/03/2001

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   The Electronic Filing Policies and Procedures Manual has been revised
   as of 12/12/2001.
   Visit the Reference section of the Electronic Filing page for
   additional information regarding electronic filing.

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   Recent enhancements to the Courts CM/ECF system require that users have
   a PACER account in addition to their CM/ECF identification name and
   password to access documents.
   More...

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   NOTE: Beginning July 1st , 2000, all new civil cases filed in the
   United States District Court for the  Northern District of Ohio will be
   placed in the Case Management/Electronic Case Filing (CM/ECF) system.
   More...

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   The United States District Court for the Northern District of Ohio
   hereby orders that, absent a  showing of good cause, all documents,
   notices and orders in all social security reviews filed in this
   district on or after January 1, 2001 shall be filed and noticed
   electronically, rather than on paper.
   More...

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   The Court is presenting a series of seminars to provide attorneys and
   their staffs with the knowledge necessary to use the Electronic Filing
   System.
   Click here for details and scheduled dates and times.

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   New Civil, Criminal, and Evidence Rules Effective December 1, 2000
   Please note that the amendments to Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure,
   Federal Rules of Civil Procedure, and Federal Rules of Evidence,
   approved by the Supreme Court on April 17, 2000, are effective December
   1, 2000. The changes  to the rules are available for viewing on the
   World Wide Web at: www.uscourts.gov/rules/approved.htm

   [ohnd_note.gif]

   The Northern District of Ohio continues to strive to provide litigants
   with the best resources available to assist in the efficient
   administration of justice through the installation of Electronic
   Courtroom facilities throughout the district. The Court strongly
   encourages attorneys to take advantage of the benefits of this new
   equipment at trial and provides training in Akron,  Cleveland, Toledo
   and Youngstown to permit attorneys to learn more about the systems
   capabilities.


